<my-features>

<div>
<h3>Room information</h3>
<p>Opened in 1965, One for the Road has 20 bedrooms, a games room, and a lounge where our residents can socialise and reminisce about the jobs they pulled.</p>
</div><!-- one -->

<div>
<h3>Day care</h3>
<p>This is for those who are less in need of care. It might be for tasks such as eating or washing, or simply for extra company&#8212;somewhere to enjoy activities and spend time with friends in a safe and supportive environment.</p>
</div><!-- two -->

<div>
<h3>Nursing care</h3>
<p>For people who need nursing care if they have certain physical conditions. This might include those with long-term conditions, those who need rehabilitation, or those with physical disabilities.</p>
</div><!-- three -->

<div>
<h3>Visiting</h3>
<p>You will need to book a visit for any old lag you&#8217;re planning to see and meet and talk with our residents in our cafe or dining room.</p>
</div><!-- four -->

<div>
<h3>Residential care</h3>
<p>For those who need help with daily activities such as eating, washing, dressing and getting around.</p>
</div><!-- five -->

</my-features>





<h2 data-function="divider">Directions <!-- @import "/partials/icon-wheelman" --></h2>

<my-directions>

<div>
<h3>By road</h3>
<p>The driving distance between London and Southend-on-Sea is 42.2 miles. Travel time is 1 hour and 3 minutes by car. Take the A13 from London. Take the 2nd exit onto A1245. Exit the roundabout onto A127. You have arrived at your destination, on the left.</p>
</div><!-- one -->

<div>
<h3>By bus</h3>
<p>There is a regular daily bus service in Southend-on-Sea and from other towns nearby. Three bus companies run the bus services in Southend-on-Sea.</p>
</div><!-- two -->

<div>
<h3>By rail</h3>
<p>One for the Road is located approximately 11 miles from Southend-on-Sea railway station. For information on rail travel information, go to the Trainline.</p>
</div><!-- three -->

</my-directions>





